Package: webserver
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         mysql-server | mariadb-server
Recommends: mysql-client | mariadb-client
Suggests: webbench
Description: High-performance C++ web server with epoll and thread pool
 WebServer is a production-ready HTTP/1.1 server featuring:
  * Epoll-based I/O multiplexing (10000+ concurrent connections)
  * Thread pool with Reactor/Proactor concurrency models
  * MySQL connection pool for efficient database operations
  * Asynchronous logging system
  * Automatic timeout connection cleanup
  * Zero-copy file transfer with memory mapping
 .
 Ideal for high-traffic websites and web applications requiring
 high performance and scalability.

Package: webbench
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Simple forking web server benchmark tool
 Webbench is a simple program for benchmarking HTTP servers using
 multiple processes to simulate concurrent user traffic.
 .
 Features:
  * Multi-process architecture for accurate load simulation
  * Support for HTTP/0.9, 1.0, and 1.1 protocols
  * Proxy support for testing through intermediaries
  * Configurable client count and test duration
 .
 Particularly useful for testing WebServer and other high-performance
 HTTP servers.
